#stance=stance1
#originalStanceText=Pro
#originalTopic=Debate:_Homosexuals_in_the_US_military
Homosexuality is not immoral, and is acceptable in the military. Former Senate Armed Services Committee Chairman John Warner, Republican of Virginia: "I respectfully, but strongly, disagree with the chairman's [Marine General Peter Pace, the chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff in 2007] view that homosexuality is immoral."[8]
